SIMPLE: isopycnic
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Isopycnic
<hw>I`so*pyc"nic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Iso-</ets>
+ Gr. <grk>pykno`s</grk> dense.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>Having
equal density, as different regions of a medium; passing through points
at which the density is equal; <as>as, an <ex>isopycnic</ex> line or
surface</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Isopycnic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Isopycnic
<hw>I`so*pyc"nic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>A line or
surface passing through those points in a medium, at which the density
is the same.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Isorcin</ent>⟦br⟧
